\subsection*{Growth feedback derivation and analysis}
Here we derive the growth rate law from equation \ref{GrR}. This term defines the contribution of the galactose metabolism to the overall cell growth rate. The cell growth rate takes into account a part relative to the Galactose metabolism ($r(s,g)$) plus an external function, $R_{ext}$, which sums up other processes that contribute to cell growth. $R_{ext}$ can  be considered constant.
